{"TopicId":190480,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How to make wings as body structures of planes?","CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-19T07:32:02Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-19T07:32:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne day, I was browsing KerbalX for learning experience from others\u0027 masterpieces, and I found this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Skyshrim/VX-4-Swiftlet\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Skyshrim/VX-4-Swiftlet\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00225RNyFTV.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/5RNyFTV.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdvantages of that aircraft considered\u00A0by me has been submitted as a comment, the most interesting part is the wings-for-structure design, which reduces weight and increase lift, that\u00A0is really a one-shot-double-kill, when I try to replicate this design on my own craft, I found it hard to balance the torque, cuz the major part of wings-for-structure is behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, and additional wings cause too much stabilizing torque and thus do harm to its maneuverability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t decide to give up this design, I am thinking about a way to make \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E almost overlapping \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E and using wings-for-structure in the mean time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny guy have ideas? I\u0027d really appreciate it if you could give some practical solution to meet both needs.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-19T13:35:30Z\u0022 title=\u002212/19/2019 01:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 19, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Scrooge\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-19T11:32:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure if I\u0027m the only one, but I don\u0027t understand what your actual question is. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-19T13:16:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223718925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576755161\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not sure if I\u0027m the only one, but I don\u0027t understand what your actual question is. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:unsure:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_unsure.png\u0022 title=\u0022:unsure:\u0022\u003EErr...my bad...sorry\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. I\u0027ve seen a plane in KerbalX which has wings as its body structure (while my\u00A0previous crafts have barrel-like MK1 inline parts as their body structures)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. This design has 2 major advantages compared to MK1 body structures as far as I concerned:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.1. Reduce the weight of the aircraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.2. Increase the total lift on the aircraft\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. However, since available positions for those wings are mostly behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, which cause too much lift behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, and thus aircraft\u00A0become too stable to be steered.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. My question is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow to utilize wings as the body of aircraft\u00A0and reduce total torque of lift in the mean time?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-19T13:33:44Z\u0022 title=\u002212/19/2019 01:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 19, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Scrooge\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-19T13:58:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223718946\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576761402\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022201766\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scrooge\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, Scrooge said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, since available positions for those wings are mostly behind the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nErrr... Why should that be the case? What keeps you from moving lift further forward or weight further backward? E.g. by adding more lift to the front of the plane or weight to the aft of the plane? In the craft from the picture e.g. you could move the structure with the air intakes/tail-part/control-fins further back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scrooge","CreatedById":201766,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-21T18:09:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223718955\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022190480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221576763903\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/19/2019 at 9:58 PM, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nErrr... Why should that be the case? What keeps you from moving lift further forward or weight further backward? E.g. by adding more lift to the front of the plane or weight to the aft of the plane? In the craft from the picture e.g. you could move the structure with the air intakes/tail-part/control-fins further back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, you are right, and I tried to adjust the level by adding weight to the tail (wings are too forward already):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221016F529C84F152E8ADCEC27BE9E0479B2C840F9\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002897994200418/1016F529C84F152E8ADCEC27BE9E0479B2C840F9/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002235D958B5AAB3A7556DFDA83FEF9FF796764CB0C2\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002897994189476/35D958B5AAB3A7556DFDA83FEF9FF796764CB0C2/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand I made this \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E aircraft with small area of central\u00A0wings, and too much additional weight for balancing\u00A0torque makes aircraft heavier than expectation, I suddenly came up with a hypothesis: maybe the weight of \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E engine made \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0too forward, so I remove the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vertical Take-Off and Landing\u0022\u003EVTOL\u003C/abbr\u003E parts and rebuild a aircraft with only central wings, and here is the result:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022668EC86ADE97EAB594B8BD41278577C7AEA1B163\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002897994177220/668EC86ADE97EAB594B8BD41278577C7AEA1B163/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002224061B70D7A2BFAF5006404A49739880085F8BD8\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/792002897994183935/24061B70D7A2BFAF5006404A49739880085F8BD8/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...since the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E cause by engines, fueltanks and air-intakes are moved backward, the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E could be easy to set with a large area of central wings behind the pod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"UncleManuel","CreatedById":201419,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-22T16:59:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not that KSP is an accurate flight simulator but basic principles still apply. I found with the Planes that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E never should be far apart, but not in the same spot either (too snappy). The two indicators are incredible helpful during the building phase...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022\u0026amp;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_cool.png\u0022 title=\u0022\u0026amp;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExtra tip: \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E should never be far off the centerline. If the engines are sitting high the plane will constantly push down. That\u0027s why I mostly use symmetrical layouts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd as always with KSP: you can attach anything to anything. That\u0027s the fun part. The hard part is structural integrity and making that pile of parts work...\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:lol:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_laugh.png\u0022 title=\u0022:lol:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002242C591EA3B731ADF03EC4916970DB65E9DAD63D0\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/767233104384192162/42C591EA3B731ADF03EC4916970DB65E9DAD63D0/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002272A79F228D72137D5FB884CD7668C07E4374DF38\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/767233104384193624/72A79F228D72137D5FB884CD7668C07E4374DF38/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022594BBA0A543DABF80E3D9A9DBC6A5E7CE3F0EE15\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/767233104384196724/594BBA0A543DABF80E3D9A9DBC6A5E7CE3F0EE15/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224490D8D82951E67CC158E33CD92906AA1B7C8B60\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/767233104384203136/4490D8D82951E67CC158E33CD92906AA1B7C8B60/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}